description: Updates the sensitivity scoring settings for an S3 bucket.

parameters.name: resourceArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the S3 bucket that the request applies to.

parameters.name: suppressDataIdentifiers
parameters.description: An array of objects, one for each custom data identifier or managed data identifier that detected a type of sensitive data to exclude from the bucket's score. To include all sensitive data types in the score, don't specify any values for this array. (dict) --- Specifies a custom data identifier or managed data identifier that detected a type of sensitive data to exclude from an S3 bucket's sensitivity score. id (string) --- The unique identifier for the custom data identifier or managed data identifier that detected the type of sensitive data to exclude from the score. type (string) --- The type of data identifier that detected the sensitive data. Possible values are: CUSTOM, for a custom data identifier; and, MANAGED, for a managed data identifier.

nested_params.name: id
nested_params.description: The unique identifier for the custom data identifier or managed data identifier that detected the type of sensitive data to exclude from the score.

nested_params.name: type
nested_params.description: The type of data identifier that detected the sensitive data. Possible values are: CUSTOM, for a custom data identifier; and, MANAGED, for a managed data identifier.
